Philip Pope is an actor who played several roles in The Hitchhiker's Guide to the Galaxy (radio series). He played one of the Krikkiters in the Tertiary Phase and two parts in the Quintessential Phase: one of the Grebulons in Fit the Twenty-Fourth and Elvis in Fit the Twenty-Sixth.

He wrote the song that was sung by the Krikkiters in the Tertiary Phase, "Under the Ink Black Sky," and was one of the three performers. He also sang it in the Quintessential Phase, this time as Elvis Presley. He also wrote the music to The Teleportation Blues.
